<br>
regarding the fetus:<br>
<br>
1.  its genetically human.  diploid, genetically distinct, etc.no one arguing this point, i trust?<br>
2.  its alive.  (perhaps someone actually doesnt understand this point yet... membrane potentials are established ca. 6 seconds after fertilization... the &quot;miracle of life&quot;... it is a living organism)<br>
<br>
now based on these tested, proven facts, a fetus is a living human being.  it is in the same category as 90 yr old cancer patients on life support,  2 year old toddlers in their mothers arms, politicians, and single mothers. <br>
<br>
the question you keep sidestepping here is: what rights are afforded a person who cannot yet make decisions for themself, canot survive without medical assistance or maternal care, and in fact cannot speak to declare its intents/desires?<br>
<br>
well... as for decision making ability: see statutory rape laws.<br>
as for medical assistance... the cancer/aids patient analogy was apt, and youve yet to refute it... fetuses, cancer patients, and aids patients are all GUARANTEED to die without medical assistance.  GUARANTEED.  somehow the amount of time it would take them to die seems to be your critical factor here?  odd.<br>
<br>
a fetus is human, living, and is a genetically distinct organism.  the issue of its consciousness or lack thereof is unprovable and untestable.<br>
<br>
so the question is:  what rights are you going to give this person whose consciousness you cannot prove?<br>
<br>
Lilum, youve asked me to prove that fetuses are people.<br>
<br>
prove to me that blacks, gays, hispanics, liberals, and communists are people. prove to me that YOU are conscious.  you somehow think you have the right to shift the burden of proof for an unprovable philosophical statement on me... but there is no burden of proof, because its unprovable. <p>Azeroeth</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualdarionshard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aldarion Shard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 6:50:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8763.topic&index=116>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a</span><hr size=1> let me tell you a true story lilum.<br>
